.TH MAILROOM 1 "April 2026" "mailroom 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mailroom \- email toolkit for AI assistants and command\-line scripting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mailroom
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-account\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mailroom
provides CLI commands for searching, reading, moving, flagging, and
replying to emails over IMAP. It can also run an MCP (Model Context
Protocol) server for integration with AI assistants.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR
Path to TOML configuration file. May also be set via the
\fBMAILROOM_CONFIG\fR environment variable.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-account\fR \fINAME\fR
Account name for multi\-account configurations. Uses the default account
if omitted.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose (debug) logging.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBlist\-accounts\fR
List configured email accounts.
.TP
\fBserver\-status\fR
Show IMAP server status and configuration.
.TP
\fBsearch\-emails\fR [\fIQUERY\fR] [\fB\-\-folder\fR \fIFOLDER\fR] [\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR]
Search for emails. Supports Gmail\-style queries (e.g.\&
\fIfrom:alice subject:invoice\fR), bare\-word text search, and raw IMAP
queries prefixed with \fIimap:\fR.
.TP
\fBmove\-email\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR \fITARGET_FOLDER\fR
Move an email to another folder.
.TP
\fBmark\-as\-read\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR
Mark an email as read.
.TP
\fBmark\-as\-unread\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR
Mark an email as unread.
.TP
\fBflag\-email\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR [\fB\-\-unflag\fR]
Flag (star) an email, or remove the flag with \fB\-\-unflag\fR.
.TP
\fBdelete\-email\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR
Delete an email.
.TP
\fBprocess\-email\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR \fIACTION\fR [\fB\-\-target\-folder\fR \fIF\fR] [\fB\-\-notes\fR \fITEXT\fR]
Process an email with a given action (move, read, unread, flag, unflag,
delete).
.TP
\fBlist\-attachments\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR
List attachments for an email.
.TP
\fBdownload\-attachment\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR \fIIDENTIFIER\fR \fISAVE_PATH\fR
Download an attachment by filename or numeric index.
.TP
\fBexport\-email\-html\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR \fISAVE_PATH\fR
Export email HTML content to a standalone file with embedded images.
.TP
\fBextract\-email\-links\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR [\fIUID\fR ...]
Extract all links from email HTML content.
.TP
\fBdraft\-reply\fR \fB\-\-folder\fR \fIF\fR \fB\-\-uid\fR \fIUID\fR \fB\-\-body\fR \fITEXT\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Draft a reply to an email. By default saves to the IMAP drafts folder.
With \fB\-\-output\fR, writes raw RFC 822 to a file or stdout (\fB\-\fR).
.TP
\fBprocess\-meeting\-invite\fR \fIFOLDER\fR \fIUID\fR [\fB\-\-availability\-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR]
Process a meeting invite and create a draft reply.
.TP
\fBmcp\fR [\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR] [\fB\-\-debug\fR] [\fB\-\-dev\fR] [\fB\-\-version\fR]
Start the MCP server. Requires the optional \fBmcp\fR Python package.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBMAILROOM_CONFIG\fR
Path to the TOML configuration file, used when \fB\-\-config\fR is not
given.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I config.toml
Default configuration file. See
.I /usr/share/doc/mailroom/examples/config.toml
for a sample.
.SH AUTHOR
Weiwu Zhang
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR imap (7),
.BR python3 (1)
